[[File:Force Trainer.jpg|thumb|Star War Force Trainer]]

<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File: NeuroSky ForceTrainer Thumb.jpg|thumb | right | Star Wars Force Trainer]]  -->
The '''Force Trainer''' is a ''[[Star Wars]]''-themed toy which creates the illusion of performing [[the Force|Force]]-powered [[telekinesis]].<ref>[http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,529539,00.html?test=latestnews New Brain-Wave Toy Lets You Do 'Jedi Mind Trick'], Fox News, June 30, 2009</ref>

The [[brain–computer interface]] toy, released was [[Uncle Milton Industries]]' Star Wars Science line in 2009, comes with a headset that claims to sense the brain's electric fields (similar to an [[Electroencephalography|EEG]]) and relays the signals to a tube that uses a fan to blow a ball into the air. The harder the user concentrates, the harder the fan blows, and the higher the ball is suspended. The voice of [[Yoda]] instructs the user on developing their skills.<ref>[http://www.boston.com/business/technology/articles/2009/06/15/may_the_force_be_with_you_for_just_130/ May the force be with you, for just $130], The Boston Globe, June 15, 2009</ref>
{{clear}}

In a 2010 episode of the [[CollegeHumor|College Humor]] series ''Bleep Bloop'', the hosts Jeff Rubin and Pat Cassels tested out the toy, even having a co-worker, Brian Murphy, play [[Brain Age]], a video game advertised as making you use your brain more, while he had the Force Trainer headset on.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IHA4j66MCa0&feature=relmfu|title=Bleep Bloop: Star Wars Force Trainer|first=|last=CollegeHumor|date=24 June 2010|publisher=|accessdate=22 December 2016|via=YouTube}}</ref>

One user of the toy argues that the brainwave effect of the Force Trainer II is fake; if the electrodes are connected directly to each other instead of being worn by the player, the game will proceed to play itself and pass all of the training exercises without any user input.<ref>{{Citation|last=Wayne Schmidt|title=Proof Force Trainer II Is Fake|date=2017-01-04|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ahbfsr87fbQ|accessdate=2017-01-09}}</ref>

